-- European markets hit by news of Gross departure
-- By Blaise Robinson
-- Fri Sep 26, 2014 09:18AM EDT
-- None



PARIS, Sept 26 (Reuters) - European shares trimmed their gains in afternoon trade as shares of German insurer Allianz <ALVG.DE> sank on news fund manager Bill Gross was leaving Allianz's asset-management unit Pimco.

Gross, one of the bond market's most renowned investors, will be joining Pimco's rival Janus Capital Group <JNS.N>, Janus said on Friday. [ID:nL2N0RR0P2] Allianz shares tumbled 6 percent, representing a wipeout in the group's market value of about 3.75 billion euros ($4.77 billion).